    <dashboard name='Market Overview' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='1'>&lt;Sheet Name&gt;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='309' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size maxheight='964' maxwidth='1416' minheight='964' minwidth='1416' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98340' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98870' x='565' y='830'>
            <zone h='3423' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98870' x='565' y='830' />
            <zone fixed-size='88' h='9129' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98870' x='565' y='4253' />
            <zone h='85788' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98870' x='565' y='13382'>
              <flipboard active-id='3' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='Market Structure Overview: Usage vs Satisfaction Landscape' captured-sheet='Brand Health Matrix' id='1' />
                  <story-point caption='Competitive Clusters and Market Segmentation' captured-sheet='Brand Health Matrix' id='2' />
                  <story-point caption='Target Brand Position Within Competitive Landscape' captured-sheet='Brand Health Matrix' id='3' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='11515' hidden='true' id='6' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='33333' x='41384' y='14419'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Baskerville'>The competitive landscape reveals a clear separation between high-performing leadership brands and lower-engagement competitors, structured across both usage penetration and customer satisfaction dimensions.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='6846' hidden='true' id='8' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='33333' x='47811' y='50622'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Baskerville'>A small subset of brands dominates the upper-right region, indicating leadership in both adoption and advocacy, while a larger group remains concentrated in lower-performance zones.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='5498' hidden='true' id='9' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='33333' x='59181' y='79149'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Baskerville'>This suggests that market success is not evenly distributed, but rather concentrated among a few key players.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='6846' hidden='true' id='10' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='33333' x='48870' y='15456'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Baskerville'>The competitive landscape can be segmented into four distinct strategic clusters based on usage penetration and customer satisfaction.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='6846' hidden='true' id='11' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='33333' x='44138' y='27905'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Baskerville'>Leadership brands occupy the high-performance quadrant, demonstrating strong balance between scale and loyalty.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='6846' hidden='true' id='12' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='33333' x='58757' y='75519'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Baskerville'>Several brands achieve high usage but relatively lower advocacy, suggesting reliance on accessibility rather than emotional strength.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='6846' id='13' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='33333' x='40254' y='19813'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Baskerville'>The target brand occupies a differentiated position within the market, reflecting a balance between moderate usage penetration and relatively strong customer satisfaction.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='6846' id='14' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='33333' x='44421' y='33817'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Baskerville'>While it does not lead in overall scale compared to dominant competitors, it demonstrates competitive strength in engagement quality, particularly in customer advocacy.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='5809' id='15' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='33333' x='48941' y='48859'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Baskerville'>This positioning indicates that the brand competes more on loyalty and experience rather than mass-market penetration.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{D09019D9-F737-4D90-B100-37A16AAD1DC4}' />
    </dashboard>
  </dashboards>
